"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=EF98C809-AE43-4880-9FBD-64459B5B35BD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fwashington-stages-a-peacetime-fiscal-blowout-3ba548d&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊社论报告：如何使国会无效。图片：彭博新闻/美联社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/washington-stages-a-peacetime-fiscal-blowout-3ba548d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/washington-stages-a-peacetime-fiscal-blowout-3ba548d<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Gift to Putin: No Uranium Mining Near the Grand Canyon]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>新政府的土地掠夺使美国更加依赖俄罗斯。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138252945701556"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138252945701556"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 6:34 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-gift-to-putin-no-uranium-mining-near-the-grand-canyon-6c1916bf"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832157?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 8 月 8 日，乔·拜登总统在亚利桑那州图萨扬的红山机场举着指定 Baaj Nwaavjo I&#39;Tah Kukveni 国家纪念碑的公告。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：约翰·洛彻/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>周二，拜登总统大笔一挥，封锁了近一百万英亩的土地，禁止开发，其中包括美国一些最丰富的铀矿床。这是政府破坏性能源政策的又一座纪念碑。</p><p> 1906 年的《古物法》允许总统留出联邦土地用于国家纪念碑，以保护历史文物。巴拉克·奥巴马(Barack Obama)利用该法律取消了数百万英亩的联邦土地用于石油和天然气开发。然而，就连他也抵制了在大峡谷外划出富含铀的土地的进步呼吁。拜登先生没有表现出这样的克制。</p><p>周二，他宣布在亚利桑那州 1,562 平方英里的土地上建立一座国家纪念碑，名为 Baaj Nwaavjo I&#39;tah Kukveni，意思是“部落漫游的地方”。白宫表示，这座纪念碑将保护“部落民族和原住民神圣的景观，并推进拜登总统的历史性气候和保护议程”。</p><p>该声明忽略了这片土地还包括美国唯一在全球市场上具有经济竞争力的高品位铀矿石来源。美国约95%用于核反应堆的铀进口，主要来自哈萨克斯坦、加拿大、俄罗斯和澳大利亚。俄罗斯是美国第三大铀来源国。</p><p>去年春天，拜登通过行政命令禁止进口俄罗斯化石燃料，但美国核电站 12% 的燃料供应仍依赖俄罗斯铀。新的国家纪念碑——拜登总统任期内的第五座纪念碑——将使美国更难取代俄罗斯的铀矿。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>致谢。</p><p>国家纪念碑未说明的目的似乎是阻止铀矿开采。亚利桑那州民主党众议员劳尔·格里哈尔瓦 (Raul Grijalva) 提出立法，永久将大峡谷地区从新的采矿权中撤回。民主党无法在国会通过这项法案，因此拜登先生通过法令这样做了。</p><p>部落声称铀矿开采可能会污染水和野生动物。但 2021 年美国地质调查局发现，尽管进行了数十年的铀矿开采，该地区的泉水和水井仍符合联邦饮用水标准。拜登总统似乎并不认为可以同时开发和保护美国的自然资源，尽管矿商几十年来一直在这样做。</p><p>进步人士希望阻止美国的所有采矿活动，包括推动绿色能源转型所需的锂和镍等关键矿物的开采。但这意味着采矿将发生在环境保护较少的国家。</p><p>目前，根据《古物法》，总统将土地从开发和公共用途中移除的权力没有任何限制。环保组织甚至认为总统不能撤销前任的任命。这种对单向行政权力的解释比大峡谷更为广泛，并且迫切需要法律挑战。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=B0B49BB4-E58D-4FC7-A236-C7F1046D346E&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fa-gift-to-putin-no-uranium-mining-near-the-grand-canyon-6c1916bf&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">回顾与展望：阿留申群岛附近的联合海军巡逻是对美国的警告和考验 图片：祖马出版社/阿拉斯加火山观测站/美联社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:34:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-gift-to-putin-no-uranium-mining-near-the-grand-canyon-6c1916bf</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-gift-to-putin-no-uranium-mining-near-the-grand-canyon-6c1916bf<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>活力</category><category>金属矿石开采</category><category>基本材料/资源</category><category>采矿/采石</category><category>有色金属矿开采</category><category>铀矿开采</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>土地利用</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>土地利用</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>活力</category><category>金属矿石开采</category><category>基础材料</category><category>资源</category><category>矿业</category><category>采石</category><category>有色金属矿开采</category><category>铀矿开采</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Judicial Politicians of Wisconsin]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>州最高法院新的进步多数从首席大法官手中夺取了权力。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136662468101230"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136662468101230"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 6:32 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-judicial-politicians-of-wisconsin-6dfb3b36"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831343?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">位于麦迪逊的威斯康星州议会大厦。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：斯科特·鲍尔/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>要了解法官政治化后会发生什么，请看一下威斯康星州新的进步最高法院多数派。上周，随着新任大法官珍妮特·普罗塔谢维奇（Janet Protasiewicz）的上任，他们以 4 比 3 成为多数派，他们的第一个行动就是一场行政政变。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>周五，四名自由派人士对法庭程序进行了修改，使他们能够篡夺首席大法官的权力，包括控制口头辩论、规则听证会和行政会议的日程。他们还发布了一项新规则，要求在多数意见形成后 7 天内提出异议。</p><p>为什么这么快就行使权力，而且没有通常的司法合议？也许是因为控制司法日历就意味着控制政治日历。</p><p>法院可能很快就会听到对该州立法地图的质疑，普罗塔谢维奇法官今年竞选最高法院席位时称这些地图“被操纵”。将异议撰写时间限制在 7 天将加快裁决的时间表，并让保守派有更少的时间整理他们的论点。想象一下，如果六名保守派大法官在美国最高法院施展这一伎俩，将会引发怎样的轩然大波。</p><p>国家党和威斯康星州民主党长期以来一直想推翻该州的立法地图，现在他们正在提高出价。竞选法律中心、Law Forward、哈佛大学选举法诊所和其他团体正在要求威斯康星州法院推翻立法地图，并发布“令状<em>保证书</em>”，要求所有州立法者，包括 2022 年 11 月当选的议员，参加竞选再次在新划定的地区。</p><p>威斯康星州最高法院最初批准了州长托尼·埃弗斯 (Tony Evers) 绘制的地图，并于 2022 年批准了当前的威斯康星州立法地图。当埃弗斯地图被美国最高法院推翻后，法院批准了目前由共和党立法机构绘制的地图。</p><p>但请愿者仍然指望他们帮助选出的新自由派法院多数派能够很快推翻地图。在“违宪配置的选区”举行的选举。请愿书称，应宣布“非法”，法院应“下令在 2024 年 11 月为所有人举行特别选举……”。 。 。州参议院选区要到 2026 年 11 月才会出现这种情况。”</p><p>请愿者建议最高法院在 2024 年 3 月 19 日之前发布裁决，这也就不足为奇了：2024 年 11 月选举的提名文件将于 4 月 15 日开始散发。</p><p>翻译：法院越早扔掉地图，民主党就能越早选出新的进步立法机构。目标是翻转足够的席位，在威斯康星州建立新的民主党立法多数。这将有助于埃弗斯推翻前州长斯科特·沃克（Scott Walker）的集体谈判改革（即第 10 号法案），并终止威斯康星州的择校计划。</p><p>威斯康星州宪法规定，州最高法院首席大法官“应是司法系统的行政首长”。现任首席大法官安妮特·齐格勒 (Annette Ziegler) 称新自由派多数派的改革是“试图削弱首席大法官作为法院管理者的宪法权威”。听起来不错。进步四人并不担心自己的政治形象，因为他们竞相将獾州变成明尼苏达州或伊利诺伊州。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F39EC653-A48E-4FB7-AF6D-1F040C95B008&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fthe-judicial-politicians-of-wisconsin-6dfb3b36&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊社论报告：Kim Strassel、Kyle Peterson、Kate Bachelder 和 Dan Henninger 的本周最佳和最差图片：路透社/美联社综合报道：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:32:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-judicial-politicians-of-wisconsin-6dfb3b36</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-judicial-politicians-of-wisconsin-6dfb3b36<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Fix the Court’ Should Fix Itself]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>左翼组织可能违反了 501(c)3 披露规则。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590136000500985346"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590136000500985346"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 6:31 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fix-the-court-should-fix-itself-788170d8"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832191?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">文件 - 2017 年 10 月 10 日日落时分看到的华盛顿最高法院。（美联社照片/J. Scott Applewhite，文件）</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：J. Scott Applewhite/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果那些攻击最高法院法官涉嫌道德过失的进步人士能够言出必行，那就太好了。以“修复法院”组织为例，该组织正在与民主党合作，通过法官的道德和信息披露规则，同时忽视披露其游说活动的要求。</p><p> Fix the Court 正在领导一场针对克拉伦斯·托马斯 (Clarence Thomas) 和塞缪尔·阿利托 (Samuel Alito) 法官的运动，他们涉嫌与亿万富翁有联系。该非营利组织是新风险基金的一个分支，该基金是由左翼营利性阿拉贝拉顾问公司支持的进步团体网络之一。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “我们是全国唯一致力于通过倡导一些简单的‘修复’来开放政府最强大、最不负责任的部分——最高法院的团体，”修复法院的网站称。 “修复”意味着减少保守派对最高法院的影响。</p><p>其中一项解决方案是参议员谢尔登·怀特豪斯 (Sheldon Whitehouse) 的《最高法院道德、回避和透明度法案》。上个月，“修复法院”执行董事加布·罗斯出现在怀特豪斯先生的播客中，“讨论如何通过立法加强法院的道德护栏”。</p><p>怀特豪斯的法案将根据国会的现行规则，为法院制定“礼物、收入和报销”的披露规则。它还将任命来自巡回上诉法院的五名首席法官组成的小组，负责听取来自 Fix the Court 等团体针对法官的道德投诉。由三名法官组成的小组将审查各方提出的回避“动议”。</p><p>目的是将道德和信息披露武器化。进步人士希望对保守派大法官提出道德指控，无论这些指控多么毫无根据，以损害他们的声誉并迫使他们回避重要案件。</p><p>然而，正如《华盛顿观察报》最近报道的那样，Fix the Court 并未遵守其应遵守的披露规则。作为 501(c)(3) 公共慈善机构，该机构可以隐藏其捐赠者的姓名。捐款还可免税。但慈善机构必须遵守政治活动的限制。</p><p>美国国税局网站指出，“如果组织的大部分活动试图影响立法（通常称为游说），则任何组织都没有资格获得第 501(c)(3) 条的资格”，其中包括敦促“公众联系、立法机构的成员或雇员”并主张“通过或否决立法”。 IRS 将“大部分”定义为支出的 20% 以上。</p><p>慈善机构必须在其 990 纳税申报表上披露是否参与政治游说。Fix 法院声称其没有就 2022 年公开披露进行游说。然而，其网站上列出了一长串其支持或反对的司法法案。</p><p>它还表示，它正在“在第 118 届国会中与议员合作，敦促司法部门采用国会议员和高级行政部门官员必须遵守的同样严格的旅行、礼品和个人招待规则”，并支持国会利用其法定权力“迫使人们接受[道德]准则。”根据国税局的定义，这看起来确实像是政治游说。</p><p>当审查员要求发表评论时，法院没有回应。针对我们的询问，它发表了董事会主席乔什·科恩的声明：</p><p> “Gabe [Roth] 和 Fix the Court 一直秉持诚信行事，当我们意识到 990 不完整时，我们就开始努力纠正它。在党派偏见占主导地位的时刻，修复最高法院是非常无党派的，它继续要求民主党和共和党总统提名的法官遵循最高的道德标准——这与我们对其他两个分支的要求相同。”</p><p>换句话说，该组织谴责大法官披露错误，但当它因同样的事情而受到指责时，它声称自己的行为是“善意的”。也许修复法院应该首先用民主党参议员的话说，在国会或国税局要求其重组之前“自我治愈”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=BA8E58C2-9DA6-441F-8E2E-AC81AF123818&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ffix-the-court-should-fix-itself-788170d8&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊社论报告：一场包装和期限限制的运动出现。图片：法新社/盖蒂图片社/美联社综合报道：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">《华尔街日报》互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/fix-the-court-should-fix-itself-788170d8</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/fix-the-court-should-fix-itself-788170d8<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>突击</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>伦理道德问题</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>社会问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>突击</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>伦理道德问题</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>社会问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Impeaching a Trump Impeachment]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>亨特·拜登的新细节证明了 2019 年臭名昭著的乌克兰通话的合理性。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590137861336404060"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590137861336404060"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/holman-w-jenkinsjr"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BI571_jenkin_AM_20180807123815.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline">作者：<span class="author" itemprop="name">小</span><span class="author" itemprop="name">霍尔曼·W·詹金斯</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 6:20 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/impeaching-a-trump-impeachment-hunter-biden-partisan-investigation-ukraine-gop-election-847d972"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831862?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 8 月 5 日，前总统唐纳德·特朗普在南卡罗来纳州哥伦比亚。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Artie Walker Jr./美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>让党派的唾沫飞扬吧，就像第一次弹劾特朗普时那样。谁在 2016 年解雇了乌克兰总检察长？原因为何？由于前亨特·拜登合伙人德文·阿彻在国会的证词，这个问题又回来了。</p><p>无论发生什么，事情都不是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>所说的那样。这也不是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/joe-biden">乔·拜登</a>所说的那样。他声称安排解雇检察官维克多·肖金，并向时任总统彼得·波罗申科发出最后通牒，这只是乔的又一个荒诞故事。几个月后，在几个西方政府的要求下，肖金被解职。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>但阿彻先生的证词驳斥了特朗普支持者所讲述的简单故事，即肖金先生被解雇是为了保护乔和亨特·拜登。阿切尔表示，肖金之所以受到乌克兰领导层的重视，正是因为他隐瞒了对布里斯马公司的长期调查，亨特是一家天然气公司的董事会成员。</p><p>这<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-wrong-impeachers-11572649090?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">符合</a>我当时的看法。拜登先生不需要做任何事情。事实上，他可以与欧盟和其他捐助者一起对肖金采取反腐败姿态，因为他知道乌克兰完全有动力保护拜登家族。</p><p>不管解雇的原因是什么，肯定不是为了给布里斯马制造麻烦。</p><p>如果是这样，民主党现在只需为亨特的商业骗局辩护，正如党内政治专家所说，兜售“进入的幻觉”。乔只需去几家餐馆、用免提电话聊聊天气、借给亨特一些白宫、空军二号等的装饰，漫不经心地煽动这种幻觉，这都是可以原谅的。</p><p>也就是说，等待其他证据失败。阿彻先生说，至少有一次，Burisma 创始人米科拉·兹洛切夫斯基 (Mykola Zlochevsky) 在喝酒时敦促亨特代表他“给 DC 打电话”，亨特照做了。一名 FBI 线人称，兹洛切夫斯基声称曾对拜登夫妇的通话进行录音，并行贿 1000 万美元。 The laptop evidence presents various complications too.</p><p> My working assumption all along, though, has been that Joe Biden wasn&#39;t so dumb as to do anything when he knew Hunter could extract millions for doing nothing.</p><p> But there&#39;s also political risk in the Justice Department&#39;s stringing out a tax investigation to allow charges related to Hunter&#39;s Burisma earnings to fall away due to the statute of limitations. Of Hunter&#39;s several windfalls, his Burisma earnings most directly leveraged his father&#39;s role, most directly link to a specific act by his father (the Shokin firing), and provide the most direct credence to Mr. Trump&#39;s first impeachment defense, concerning his phone call to President Zelensky fishing for information about Biden dealings in Ukraine. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More Business World</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/its-doj-vs-doj-in-the-2024-race-hunter-joe-biden-trump-indictment-smith-429971ee?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">It&#39;s DOJ vs. DOJ in the 2024 Election</a> <span class="date">August 4, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ai-is-hollywoods-fake-villain-unions-strike-actors-writers-ai-jobs-studios-9cdb3ab4?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">AI Is Hollywood&#39;s Fake Villain</a> <span class="date">August 1, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-is-a-geopolitical-disaster-biden-plea-deal-russia-twitter-4f2653e6?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Hunter Biden Is a Geopolitical Disaster</a> <span class="date">July 28, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> There&#39;s some new news here. Mr. Trump may well have been informed by Attorney General William Barr</p> about the Burisma insider who spoke to the FBI—which means Mr. Trump both can keep a secret and had a stronger foundation for his request to Mr. Zelensky, whose cooperation he sought in an FBI investigation that we now know was under way in response to the confidential informant&#39;s testimony.<p></p><p> Hmmm.</p><p> The White House&#39;s latest defense implicitly allows that Joe may have discussed business with Hunter but he wasn&#39;t “in business” with Hunter. Plenty of room to maneuver is permitted if the facts show Joe did everything and anything to facilitate Hunter&#39;s “illusion of access” short of selling an official act or joining Hunter&#39;s payroll.</p><p> Can Mr. Biden be re-elected despite all this? Yup, just as Mr. Trump can be elected from prison. Silence reigns in Democratic circles, though, because it also increases the possibility that Mr. Biden will become “indisposed” and bow out of the race.</p><p> It occurs to some that Jack Smith, the Justice Department special counsel, is but the executor of a policy decision made elsewhere, <a href="https://twitter.com/mrddmia/status/1688319081383129088" target="_blank" class="icon none">telegraphed</a> in the</p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NYT" class="company-name">New York Times</a> in April 2022, by Mr. Biden to run up the charges against Mr. Trump as part of his election strategy.<p></p><p> Mr. Biden plays dice with the country because he thinks Mr. Trump is the one GOP nominee he can defeat.</p><p> A flutter of hope passed through the electorate with the prospect of a TV debate between Florida&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/ron-desantis">Ron DeSantis</a> and California&#39;s Gavin Newsom, perhaps starting a groundswell for an alternative presidential slate in 2024. A widely read <a href="https://www.tabletmag.com/sections/arts-letters/articles/david-garrow-interview-obama" target="_blank" class="icon none">interview</a> with Obama biographer David Garrow, of “Eyes on the Prize” and Martin Luther King Jr. biography fame, put the question of Obama-style cynicism on the table. Joe Biden cultivated a belief in millions of voters that he would he wave away their student debt though he knew he couldn&#39;t. Mr. Biden is doing all he can now to make sure the country must choose between him and Mr. Trump. But many a slip occurs between cup and lip—a health crisis, a Hunter blowup, a Trump acquittal, a reverse in Ukraine—that could make Messrs. Biden and Smith the men who delivered the White House to Donald Trump. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=5DE7BC77-6402-4B80-A5E9-9E8AC3644D45&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fimpeaching-a-trump-impeachment-hunter-biden-partisan-investigation-ukraine-gop-election-847d972&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：司法部加速法律攻势。 Images: Zuma Press/AFP/Getty Images Composite: Mark Kelly <span class="imageCredit">The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:20:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/impeaching-a-trump-impeachment-hunter-biden-partisan-investigation-ukraine-gop-election-847d972</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/impeaching-a-trump-impeachment-hunter-biden-partisan-investigation-ukraine-gop-election-847d972<category> impeachment</category><category> partisan</category><category>总统</category><category>gop</category><category>辩论</category><category>tax investigation</category><category> ukraine</category><category> testimony</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>Corporate/Industrial News</category><category> Political/General News</category><category> Impeachment</category><category> Political Appointments/Terminations</category><category> Politics/International Relations</category><category> Domestic Politics</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Commentaries/Opinions</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Joe Biden</category><category> corporate</category><category> industrial news</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category> political appointments</category><category> terminations</category><category>政治</category><category>international relations</category><category> domestic politics</category><category> content types</category><category> commentaries</category><category> opinions</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e executive news filter</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘In My Room’ on the Riverfront]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Walking along the Hudson, I heard the Beach Boys classic. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590128440863742002"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590128440863742002"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Bob Greene</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 8, 2023 6:19 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-my-room-on-the-riverfront-music-beach-boys-lyrics-new-york-1c4841da"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831902?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Brian Wilson on a radio show in Luxembourg, Nov. 1, 1964.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: RB/Redferns</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> I was walking along the Hudson River in lower Manhattan when I decided to turn onto Pier 45, a promenade that allows pedestrians to get close to the water. Scores of people were on the pier, savoring a summer Sunday afternoon.</p><p> At the far end I heard someone singing lyrics that I have known for 60 years: “There&#39;s a world where I can go, and tell my secrets to . 。 。 ”</p><p> It was “In My Room,” the 1963 Beach Boys song in which Brian Wilson&#39;s pure, youthful voice told a haunting story of finding solace behind a closed door.</p><p> “In this world I lock out all my worries and my fears . 。 ”。</p><p> It wasn&#39;t Mr. Wilson&#39;s voice I was hearing on Pier 45, though. Someone else was singing a live version of the song.</p><p> An African-American man, around 70, sat alone at an electric keyboard. He didn&#39;t face in, toward the people walking on the pier, as he sang, but out, toward the river itself.</p><p> Mr. Wilson, 81, has been ailing lately. He isn&#39;t touring or performing in public. Those who love his music miss him.</p><p> And here was this man on the pier, singing to the water. Singing the words on which Brian&#39;s voice had conferred a kind of immortality. I continued my walk and left the pier, but quickly decided to circle back and talk with the man.</p><p> His name was Daniel Al-Mateen,</p> and he was 74. He liked to play and sing, he said, and his favorite genres were rhythm-and-blues and reggae.<p></p><p> I told him that as a friend of some of Brian&#39;s band members, I knew that Brian would be warmed to hear about this solo performance on the Hudson, and that I was pretty sure I could get word to him. But I had a question: Why “In My Room,” in this place, on this day?</p><p> Mr. Al-Mateen said he had been feeling especially wistful about all the losses in his life as the years have passed. His mother, gone. His father, gone. His brother, gone. His sister, gone. His best friends, gone. His wife, gone.</p><p> So he put his keyboard and a power pack into a shopping cart and wheeled it out to the end of the pier. “In My Room,” he had long thought, was “so beautiful, so poignant in its seeming simplicity.” He wanted to remind himself that “the people we have loved may have left us, but they are with us forever, every time we think about them.”</p><p> “Do my dreaming and my scheming, lie awake and pray / Do my crying and my sighing, laugh at yesterday . 。 ”。</p><p> I asked him about the setting: Why, with the private thoughts that were filling him, had he left his own room to come sing “In My Room” to the river?</p><p> “You don&#39;t need a castle,” he said. “You just need a place where you can go to stay out of the maelstrom.”</p><p> I promised him I would find a way to let Brian know about his lovely rendition on this New York day.</p><p> “Please tell him thank you,” Mr. Al-Mateen said. “Please tell him thank you for everything.”</p><p> <em>Mr. Greene&#39;s books include “When We Get to Surf City: A Journey Through America in Pursuit of Rock and Roll, Friendship, and Dreams.”</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F39EC653-A48E-4FB7-AF6D-1F040C95B008&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fin-my-room-on-the-riverfront-music-beach-boys-lyrics-new-york-1c4841da&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊社论报告：Kim Strassel、Kyle Peterson、Kate Bachelder 和 Dan Henninger 的本周最佳和最差图片：路透社/美联社综合报道：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:19:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-my-room-on-the-riverfront-music-beach-boys-lyrics-new-york-1c4841da</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-my-room-on-the-riverfront-music-beach-boys-lyrics-new-york-1c4841da<category>音乐</category><category>纽约</category><category>海滩男孩</category><category>sogn</category><category>生活</category><category>歌词</category><category>immortality</category><category> Political/General News</category><category> Politics/International Relations</category><category> Domestic Politics</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Commentaries/Opinions</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>政治</category><category>international relations</category><category> domestic politics</category><category> content types</category><category> commentaries</category><category> opinions</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e executive news filter</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Recoding America’ Review: A Tale of the Tape]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The bigger obstacle to modernizing Washington and making government more efficient is politics, not bureaucratic red tape. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590128081788835478"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831957?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Getty Images/iStockphoto </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590128081788835478"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Mark P. Mills</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 8, 2023 6:18 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/recoding-america-review-a-tale-of-the-tape-449e8b3c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Apparently the swamp in Washington, DC, is not a political but a bureaucratic mire. As Jennifer Pahlka writes in “Recoding America: Why Government Is Failing in the Digital Age and How We Can Do Better,” bureaucracy “bogs down our systems,” creating a chasm “between policy intentions and actual outcomes.” She believes we “desperately need to simplify and rationalize” it all because the bureaucratic “implementation crisis threatens our democracy.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/b2d574cb-e749-4c96-a034-7b43fc3c907f.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Given the allusion to computer code in her book&#39;s title, you&#39;d be forgiven for thinking that “Recoding America” is about algorithms and artificial intelligence put in the service of taming, not draining, the swamp. But the term “artificial intelligence” appears only twice here, both times to dismiss its relevance. While that omission may be refreshing in the wake of all the ChatGPT hype, it&#39;s also puzzling given how Ms. Pahlka asserts that our “digital age is different from previous eras.”</p><p> Among her many roles in government, Ms. Pahlka has served as President Barack Obama&#39;s deputy chief technology officer for government innovation. Most of her book is a chronicle of her experiences working on various task forces for President Obama and California&#39;s Gov. Gavin Newsom. There are her journeys through bureaucracies involving the reclassifying of criminal records that have been rendered moot by California&#39;s marijuana legalization; implementing ObamaCare; reforming the Veterans Administration; taming the Medicare morass; and, most recently, distributing California&#39;s gusher of Covid unemployment payments. Ms. Pahlka details the “messy task of [policy] implementation through digital technology,” as well as the challenges created by “archaeological” layers of legacy computer systems and bureaucratic processes that bog things down.</p><p> Ms. Pahlka saw firsthand the “gap between policy intentions and actual outcomes” and “the famous slowness of bureaucracy.” One cannot resist paraphrasing the author&#39;s former boss: “The 1300s are calling and they want their bureaucratic characterizations back.” In 1321, Dante, himself a Florentine bureaucrat, wrote “The Divine Comedy,” which frames Hell as the epitome of bureaucracy. And that was before the invention of the printing press and its epic contribution of paperwork. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831988?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jennifer Pahlka</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Fisher Studios</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> For those not steeped in the modern bureaucratic process and its intersection with the arcana of computer systems, Ms. Pahlka&#39;s clear, diarylike explanations of (and frustrations with) bureaucracy are illuminating. As she notes, it&#39;s a daunting task even to get an accurate count of the number of eligible recipients for government largess. While her concern for quickly and fairly delivering government services is universally shared, it&#39;s in the procedures used to get “the outcomes the democratic process has agreed upon” where we find the devil-in-the-details truism.</p><p> As advice for well-meaning bureaucrats, Ms. Pahlka admiringly quotes Gen. Stanley McChrystal&#39;s dictum: “Don&#39;t follow my orders, follow the orders I would have given you if I were there and knew what you know.” But that is precisely where the battles over bureaucratic authority are being fought. As Ms. Pahlka observes, Republicans are opposed to “federal activism” and look for “ways to curb the power” of agencies. Democrats, meanwhile, want “administrative agencies to be able to exercise their own judgment.” That&#39;s no mere detail; it&#39;s the essence of the political debate over the administrative state.</p><p> Ms. Pahlka sees two main problems with today&#39;s bureaucracy: a lack of sufficient “technological know-how” in the workforce, and too much outsourcing. “Why do we treat the experts we do have with so little regard?” Ms. Pahlka asks. “It wasn&#39;t always that way.” Indeed, that&#39;s the core of the debate of our times; serious tomes have been devoted to that question.</p><p> Ms. Pahlka&#39;s proffered solutions include improving the bureaucratic “culture” with more internal training programs, more tech talent and less outsourcing. She suggests that the government seek out the kind of young graduates—as identified by a survey of Stanford undergraduate students—who prioritize a project&#39;s mission ahead of building their own skills or compensation.</p><p> The debate over outsourcing is not new. Among the many known benefits of outsourcing is that contractors can be more easily held to account and fired when underperforming. When it comes to the US government, however, insourcing all outsourced labor would expand the civil-service workforce from today&#39;s three million people to about 10 million. Moving in that direction would be a political issue of consequence.</p><p> But Ms. Pahlka is onto something. Before Congress created the Office of the President in 1939, for example, a president had but a handful of advisers and personal staff. Today that one small office, among the dozens of administrative agencies, has a $1.5 billion budget and more than 3,000 employees (only a few of which require Senate approval). The world and the economy are bigger now, but bureaucratic expansion has been incommensurate in scale, complexity and authority.</p><p> Ms. Pahlka&#39;s book is a cri de coeur for better “product delivery” from the now massive labyrinth of government services. Count me among those who believe the artificial-intelligence revolution could unlock some bureaucratic transparency and superior service delivery. But whether that will happen, or whether the bog will assimilate yet another technological revolution, is a matter of politics, not process.</p><p> <em>Mr. Mills, a senior fellow at the Manhattan Institute, is a partner at Montrose Lane, an energy-tech venture fund, and the author of “The Cloud Revolution.”</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 22:18:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/recoding-america-review-a-tale-of-the-tape-449e8b3c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/recoding-america-review-a-tale-of-the-tape-449e8b3c<category>图书</category><category>Political/General News</category><category> Arts/Entertainment</category><category> Politics/International Relations</category><category> Domestic Politics</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Exclusion Filter</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>政治</category><category>international relations</category><category> domestic politics</category><category> content types</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e exclusion filter</category><category>评论</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Santa Fe Opera Reviews: ‘Orfeo,’ ‘Pelléas et Mélisande,’ ‘Rusalka,’ ‘The Flying Dutchman’ and ‘Tosca’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在今年的音乐节上，蒙特威尔第关于在黑社会失去恋人的神话登上了舞台；德彪西的象征主义故事在管弦乐中取得了胜利；德沃夏克的童话故事发生了弗洛伊德式的转变； and more. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590138142555787492"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831075?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">卢克·哈尼什、罗兰多·维拉宗、劳伦·斯诺弗、卢克·埃尔默和勒布</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：柯蒂斯·布朗</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590138142555787492"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者：<span class="author" itemprop="name">海蒂·威尔森</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 5:42 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/santa-fe-opera-reviews-orfeo-pelleas-et-melisande-rusalka-the-flying-dutchman-and-tosca-90e417bc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><em>新墨西哥州圣达菲</em></p><p>今年夏天，圣达菲歌剧院上演了蒙特威尔第的<strong>《奥菲欧》</strong> ，并由尼科·穆利 (Nico Muhly) 进行了全新编配。 《奥菲欧》（1607 年）是最早的歌剧之一，通常使用古乐器演奏。穆利先生足智多谋的版本利用现代歌剧管弦乐队的工具捕捉了这些乐器的音色和透明度。他对声音的选择——例如连续奏的低风和竖琴；一把小提琴奏出凄美的时刻；钢片琴和钢琴的色彩——总是适合当下，支持声线，并且永远不会陷入过度的浪漫主义。我只错过了为卡隆特这个角色伴奏的皇家风琴的刺耳刺耳声。在公司音乐总监兼早期曲目专家 Harry Bicket 的带领下，《奥菲欧》以新的面貌保留了 17 世纪的冲动。</p><p>饰演奥菲欧的罗兰多·维拉松则没那么成功。近年来，男高音的声音变得更低沉、阴暗，适合这个角色的男中音，但他的音色却刺耳而粗暴。奥菲欧的音乐应该是迷人的；我们得到了戏剧性的取而代之。 Lauren Snouffer 饰演介绍故事的 La Musica 和护送 Orfeo 前往地狱之门的 Speranza，声音可爱、飘逸； Paula Murrihy（《La Messaggera》）和 Blake Denson（《Plutone》）也很出色。</p><p>这部深思熟虑的制作由尤瓦尔·沙龙 (Yuval Sharon) 执导，亚历克斯·施韦德 (Alex Schweder) 和马修·约翰逊 (Matthew Johnson) 负责视觉环境，中濑由纪 (Yuki Nakase Link) 负责灯光，为现实世界/地下世界的过渡提供了巧妙的解决方案。牧羊人的合唱团在一个绿色的半球体上及其周围欢腾。然后球体逐渐升起，大片织物在其下方展开，奥菲欧在黑暗中悬挂在吊带上，向卡隆特唱出了他的恳求。诸神似乎更强大，因为他们是看不见的。黑暗地下世界的居民戴着别致的发光头饰（卡洛斯·J·索托设计了服装）。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831064?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">休·蒙塔古·伦德尔和萨曼莎·汉基在《佩利亚斯与梅丽桑德》中</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：柯蒂斯·布朗</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>在由 Netia Jones（导演、布景、服装和投影设计师）制作的德彪西的<strong>《佩利亚斯与梅丽桑德》</strong>中，涉及现代性与自然的有毒冲突的潜台词读起来不够清晰。这个象征主义故事的背景似乎是一个黑暗的地下室，通过一对螺旋楼梯到达，里面有一个大型旋转玻璃容器，也可以用作床。戏的前半段，草青；第二次，它枯萎变黄。一条小溪沿着舞台的前缘流过；令人费解的是，三个主要角色都有替身在后台表演他们的场景。阿克尔、戈洛和梅丽桑德在生病或受伤时都接受了氧气治疗。有计算机代码、科学图表和管道的投影；就连水和树的形象也显得阴郁。</p><p>然而，在音乐上，这是一次胜利。比基特先生为管弦乐队带来了明显的清晰度，通过声音细节反映了角色未言明的情感，而不是沉迷于朦胧、非特定的声音。扎卡里·尼尔森（Zachary Nelson）出色地扮演了饱受折磨的戈洛德（Golaud），当他试图找出真相但未果时，他柔软的男中音变得绝望。萨曼莎·汉基（Samantha Hankey）饰演的梅丽桑德（Mélisande）丰富而明亮的中音使她更具人性而不是妖怪；休·蒙塔古·伦德尔 (Huw Montague Rendall) 引起了佩利亚斯对她感情的觉醒。雷蒙德·阿塞托（Raymond Aceto）扮演阿克尔（Arkel），一个没有权力的国王。饰演吉纳维芙的苏珊·格雷厄姆饰演的女中音已经失去了光彩，但她穿着水绿色丝绸礼服看起来很棒，这似乎象征着这个家庭与自然世界的最后联系。高音凯埃德加是一个强壮的伊尼奥德。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831068?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 《鲁莎卡》中的艾琳·佩雷斯</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：柯蒂斯·布朗</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>大卫·庞特尼 (David Pountney) 创作的德沃夏克童话<strong>《鲁莎卡》</strong>也需要预先掌握信息才能充分理解。但即使没有这一点，它在戏剧上也比《佩利亚斯》更清晰。该剧以 1900 年左右的维也纳精神病院为背景，通过弗洛伊德的视角探讨了水仙女鲁莎卡对人类形态和灵魂的渴望——从童年到成年的暴力和混乱的性转变。有趣的布景（莱斯利·特拉弗斯饰演）从一间整齐的白色房间，里面有壁橱和抽屉，到了王子的宫殿，里面的玻璃陈列柜里陈列着他的其他女性征服物。在第三幕中，当王子和露莎卡的一切都崩溃了时，箱子是空的，而且混乱地倾斜。玛丽-珍妮·莱卡 (Marie-Jeanne Lecca) 的维多利亚时代服装凸显了成年女性控制一切的力量：女巫杰兹巴巴 (Ježibaba) 身穿黑色紧身胸衣，红色骑马服，搭配高筒靴和马鞭，给这位外国公主带来了一种施虐狂的感觉。</p><p>歌手们展现了人物的复杂性，超越了他们童话般的身份。艾琳·佩雷斯 (Ailyn Pérez) 是一位热情的鲁萨尔卡 (Rusalka)，在第三幕中尤其有力，她询问王子为何背叛她。雷汉·布莱斯·戴维斯 (Raehann Bryce-Davis) 给 Ježibaba 带来了巨大的声音和近乎滑稽的虚荣心；罗伯特·沃森把王子塑造成一个软弱的人，尽管他高声咆哮。而饰演沃德尼克的詹姆斯·克雷斯韦尔（James Creswell）——措辞出色——只能威胁要对那些伤害他女儿的人进行报复，因为他被困在轮椅上。玛丽·伊丽莎白·威廉姆斯的刺耳音色很适合这位专横的外国公主。指挥家利迪亚·扬科夫斯卡娅（Lidiya Yankovskaya）捕捉到了乐谱中欢快的民间色彩部分以及其扫弦和抒情。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831061?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 《飞翔的荷兰人》中的莫里斯·罗宾逊和合唱团</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：柯蒂斯·布朗</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>在很大程度上，除了瓦格纳的<strong>《飞翔的荷兰人》之外，公司管弦乐团这一季的声音比近年来更加优美。</strong>由托马斯·古吉斯 (Thomas Guggeis) 指挥，整场演出声音喧闹，没有任何表现力的微妙之处。主唱都是瓦格纳人，拥有出色的音域、呼吸控制和音量，似乎试图在分贝水平上与管弦乐队相匹配。作为荷兰人，尼古拉斯·布朗利在开始他的开场咏叹调“Die Frist ist um”时听起来令人毛骨悚然，但它很快就变得具有攻击性，而不是令人兴奋。莫里斯·罗宾逊（达兰德）、艾尔扎·范登希弗（森塔）和查德·谢尔顿（埃里克）也受到类似的困扰。只有比勒·布鲁利（舵手）逃脱了这一命运——他的歌谣很简短。 《荷兰人》需要的不仅仅是一点美声精神；这里没有什么可吃的。</p><p>大卫·奥尔登（David Alden）丑陋而更新的制作与硬派的音乐才能相匹配。保罗·斯坦伯格的布景似乎是用集装箱建造的； 《旋转之歌》中的女合唱团在某种工业工厂里工作，穿着防护装备（康斯坦斯·霍夫曼制作了服装），像机器人一样移动。其他合唱场景除了震耳欲聋之外还很混乱，水手们在舞台上打滚。第三幕的聚会是一场狂欢，水手们和女人们试图唤醒荷兰人号的船员。奇怪的是，每个人都背对着荷兰人几乎看不见的船（玛克辛·布拉汉姆被认为是编舞者）。角色场景的方向很少甚至不存在。最有趣的时刻是一些僵尸定期将荷兰人的宝藏搬上搬下舞台。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831058?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 《托斯卡》中的利亚·霍金斯</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：柯蒂斯·布朗</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>普契尼的<strong>《托斯卡》</strong>也难以接受。设计师阿什利·马丁-戴维斯 (Ashley Martin-Davis) 的德·基里科 (De Chirico) 风格的布景，由艾伦·哈恩 (Allen Hahn) 精心打光，效果不错，但他的 1930 年代女主角服装并没有让主角莉亚·霍金斯 (Leah Hawkins) 满意，而基思·华纳 (Keith Warner) 的导演让托斯卡 (Tosca) 成为一个虚荣的自我主义者，没有脆弱性，而斯卡皮亚 (雷金纳德 (Reginald))小史密斯（Smith Jr.））是一个斜视、翻白眼的性狂。约书亚·格雷罗 (Joshua Guerrero) 的卡瓦拉多西 (Cavaradossi) 相对来说是无可挑剔的。他的《E lucevan le stelle》是当晚唯一的音乐高潮。约翰·菲奥雷的指挥——第一幕中缓慢缓慢，第二幕和第三幕中稍显轻松——反映了整个制作的混乱。本赛季将持续到8月26日。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Ms.威尔森为《华尔街日报》撰写歌剧文章，也是《疯狂场景与出口咏叹调：纽约市歌剧院之死与美国歌剧的未来》（大都会出版社）一书的作者。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 21:42:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/santa-fe-opera-reviews-orfeo-pelleas-et-melisande-rusalka-the-flying-dutchman-and-tosca-90e417bc</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/santa-fe-opera-reviews-orfeo-pelleas-et-melisande-rusalka-the-flying-dutchman-and-tosca-90e417bc<category> arts in review</category><category> Political/General News</category><category> Arts/Entertainment</category><category>音乐</category><category>Opera</category><category>剧院</category><category>Content Types</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Exclusion Filter</category><category>评论</category><category>Arts in Review</category><category> SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>歌剧</category><category>剧院</category><category>content types</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e exclusion filter</category><category>评论</category></item></channel></rss>